				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Will EQ2 Kill EQ before it's ever released?<a name="32679"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 3 04 12:49 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm guessing they may want to steal their customer base, before someone else does.
<br />

<br />
Its the classic battle, you got a good thing going and everyone wants a piece of the action. I don't blame Sony for wanting to hold on to a Lion's share of that action.
<br />

<br />
People play EQ for very different reasons. Some of us live and thrive on the end game, some of us don't care for it and have 30 something under 60 alts. Many fall in between.
<br />

<br />
Some want to group for half a day at a time, or raid for 10 hours straight, some can only and/or only want play  solo for 30 minute to an hour spurts.
<br />

<br />
I ran into a warrior the other day in SK at the spires. She was doing her laundry while playing EQ...kill  a gnoll, fold the last load, kill a gnoll put in a new load.
<br />

<br />
The point is, everyone wants a little something different, with the huge stakes at hand, its worth trying to supply different strokes for different folks.
<br />

<br />
At least thats my take. When the servers were down after the patch, I loaded Diablo, of all things...its not that bad of a break from the complexity of EQ.
<br />

<br />
I just hope they don't try to hard, pleasing everyone (just me, lol) that the whole mess takes a dive...but if they do, there are always my RL diversions.)
<br />

<br />
If you remember the Luclin expansion....this isn't quite that bad...but every huge EQ patch brings problems...it always has, some more than others.  This one is so screwed up in so many ways (geez, you can get killed as a newbie trying to ride the lifts in Kelethin!) that it is gonna be a major effort and time to iron it out.</span></td>
